1.10	Guion_S._Bluford_Jr.	Guion Bluford	Guion Stewart “Guy” Bluford, Jr. (born November 22, 1942), is an engineer, retired Colonel from the United States Air Force and a former NASA Astronaut. He participated in four Space Shuttle flights between 1983 and 1992. In 1983, as a member of the crew of the space shuttle Challenger on mission STS-8, Bluford became the first African American in space, and the second person of African ancestry, after the Cuban cosmonaut Arnaldo Tamayo Méndez.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/04/Guion_Bluford.jpg/220px-Guion_Bluford.jpg
